texts.orig: I found a really helpful tip on  Xaprb  for comparing result sets in MySQL:
texts.text: I found a really helpful tip on  Xaprb  for comparing result sets in MySQL:

texts.label: code
texts.orig:
mysql> pager md5sum -
PAGER set to 'md5sum -'
mysql> select * from test;
a09bc56ac9aa0cbcc659c3d566c2c7e4  -
4096 rows in set (0.00 sec)
texts.text:
mysql> pager md5sum -
PAGER set to 'md5sum -'
mysql> select * from test;
a09bc56ac9aa0cbcc659c3d566c2c7e4  -
4096 rows in set (0.00 sec)

texts.label: text
texts.orig: It's a quick way to determine if you have two tables that are properly in sync. Although there are  better ways  to compare tables in replicated environments, this method can get it done pretty quickly.
texts.text: It's a quick way to determine if you have two tables that are properly in sync. Although there are  better ways  to compare tables in replicated environments, this method can get it done pretty quickly.
